PR odoc-driver:

The bug. In odoc-driver's src/driver/odoc_units_of.ml, base_args builds each unit's link path by adding every library of the package (pkg.Packages.libraries) to lib_deps, rather than just the unit's actual dependencies. When a package ships two sibling libraries that expose the same wrapped module name but don't depend on each other — e.g. eliom.server and eliom.client, both wrapped as Eliom with identically-named submodules — every unit then gets both libraries on its -L path. At link time, a module that exists in both and whose expansion goes through shared signature/functor units (a functor result like Eliom.Content.Html) resolves to the wrong sibling: the client Eliom.Content.Html rendered the server's structure (it showed Printer and was missing Manip/To_dom). The one-line fix is to link each unit against lib_deps only (its own library + its declared deps), which is what the includes line just above already does.

Repro (real). opam pin add eliom git+https://github.com/ocsigen/eliom#deriving-mli-odoc, then odoc_driver eliom --remap: eliom.client/Eliom/Content/Html/ lists Printer (server-only) and lacks Manip (client-only). With the patch, the client page correctly shows Manip/To_dom/Of_dom. (Minimal synthetic version: one package, two (wrapped true) libraries both producing module Foo with a same-named submodule Foo.M of different content, no dep between them → a's Foo.M page renders b's Foo.M.)
