PR jsoo

Thanks @hhugo! Both addressed, and I pushed a few related cleanups:

1. check_manual_links.sh: internal references (`{!…}` / `{{!…}}` / manual pages) are now checked by odoc itself: dune `build @doc` fails on any unresolved ref. So I've repurposed the script to check external links only (the one thing odoc doesn't do), scanning the .mld manual for `{{:http…}` and checking them.

2. Local preview: good point. wodoc build now has a `--local` flag that fetches the shared assets (/css/…, /img/…) next to the output so the site renders offline:

```
wodoc build --config doc/wodoc --label dev --out _doc-site/dev \
  --menu https://ocsigen.org/wodoc/menu.html --local
cd _doc-site && python3 -m http.server   # http://localhost:8000/dev/js_of_ocaml/
```

Other changes since your review:

 - The per-project doc machinery is gone: no more build.sh, template.html, leftnav.html, gen-manual-nav.py, menu.wiki, resolve-siblings.py or *-highlight.js. It's all driven by one declarative config, doc/wodoc, consumed by wodoc build (which runs dune build @doc @doc-manual, themes every page, generates the nav, resolves cross-package refs, and ships a default syntax-highlight starter covering the eliom/lwt/js_of_ocaml ppx syntaxes).
 - The CI (doc.yml) now just calls wodoc build directly (no wrapper script), fetching the shared menu from its single canonical copy in ocsigen.github.io.
 - The PR description is updated to match.

One thing worth mentioning: in the .mld manual you can use `{%wodoc:…%}` markers to add CSS classes/containers; stock odoc drops them, so the same sources stay plain on ocaml.org and render themed here.
